post_text: Hello K-8 families, we just wanted to thank you for being patient and understanding while we worked through the pick up/drop off issues. We are getting into a routine and making much better time. It’s very helpful when vehicles pull all the around the loop before letting kids out. This keeps the flow of traffic moving while allowing us to be as quick as possible and maintain safety. It’s a great day to be a Cardinal!

post_text: Don’t forget, it is voting day!
shared_text:
Johannesburg-Lewiston Area Schools
June 23 at 4:15 PM ·

Hello families and Cardinal Community!

While there are many unknowns as we look to the 2020-2021 school year, there are a few things we can control. The Board has decided to move forward with the request for a Bond. Nothing has changed from the original information, the bond was just moved from the May ballot to the August ballot due to concerns about voting during the Covid pandemic. Due to rules for elections, the ballot language had to be approved by the Board in May for August. This video explains the bond proposal in more detail. Please contact any School Board member or the Superintendent with questions about the bond proposal. Thank you for being Cardinal families! Johannesburg-Lewiston is the Best Place to Learn!

shared_text:
Stone-Well Media
July 18 at 11:13 AM ·

This year has been....Interesting. For a moment there it looked like the graduating class of Johannesburg/Lewiston schools we'rent going to get their moment they had worked so hard for these past twelve years. Covid had stolen the show once again.

Through zoom calls and through a lot of hard work the JLAS staff pulled together an amazing idea; A traveling graduation so that each student would see their accomplishments celebrated like so many graduating classes before them. Even more special than that, each student had their parents, grandparents, friends and even pets watch them receive their diploma and walk across the stage!

Stone-Well Media was overjoyed to be a part of this VERY cool and unique day! Thanks again to all the JLAS school staff that made this happen and a HUGE congrats to each and every student that graduated. YOU DID IT!!

Johannesburg-Lewiston Area Schools
May 8 at 9:57 AM ·

"Even though we are all apart, thank you for continuing to TEACH with all of your HEART!" HEART. That's what makes our Johannesburg-Lewiston Area Schools the best place to learn. The connections, relationships, and care for every staff member and child is what set our schools apart. I am proud to work here and am proud to have my children go to school here. Thank you to all of our staff in this Teacher Appreciation Week. Each and everyone is so important to the well-being of us all. I speak for many when I say, We can't wait to be back TOGETHER again!

Hang in there Cardinal families and Teachers! Please continue to talk to your teachers and other school members who may be reaching out. We want to keep our connections alive and well.

Johannesburg-Lewiston Area Schools
March 30 at 9:23 AM ·

Good morning Cardinal families!

Don't forget today is MONDAY - food day! Pick up at our Lewiston building from 11am-12pm and at the Johannesburg building from 3-4pm. If you need assistance getting your food, call 732-1773, ext. 2113.

Also, in line with the CDC and the Governor's order, our school and all facilities are CLOSED, except to our essential staff. PLEASE stay off the playgrounds, ball fields, and track. Our gyms and weight rooms are closed to all while we ride out COVID-19. Our maintenance and janitorial staff are working hard to keep all areas clean and germ free.
Thank you for understanding.
